Press Releases.Title: No New Cases of Locally Transmitted Covid-19 Infection (29 Oct)
Press Releases.MainContent:
1.      As of 29 October 2020, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed that there are no new cases of locally transmitted COVID-19 infection. 

2.      There are 7 imported cases, who had all been placed on Stay-Home Notice upon arrival in Singapore.

3.      We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight.

 

 

MINISTRY OF HEALTH
29 OCTOBER 2020
